 MALALANE – A motorist sped down Air Street, narrowly avoiding pedestrians and hit a fence near TOPS at the Inkwazi Centre on Friday afternoon. The accident, which took place around 15:40,  was captured on the centre’s CCTV cameras and was shared on owner Lex Hollmann’s Facebook page and YoutTube channels the next day.  This isn’t the first time motorists speeding down this road have caused accidents or narrowly avoided it, despite the three sets of traffic lights installed as traffic calming measures. READ: Upgrades to improve traffic safety around shopping centre Hollmann says the motorist was travelling around 95km/h, by his calculations. He also mentioned that the scene was quickly cleared. WATCH: Armed robbery in Malalane It is not yet known whether a case was opened at the police station.